        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 8:18PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 817 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located near Batavia, moving
east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning
is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fayetteville, Chasetown, Batavia, Clermont County Airport,
Owensville, Newtonsville, Lake Lorelei, St. Martin, and Perintown.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
